Titolo: Mr. Robot and His Robot Factory

Anno: 1983

Descrizione: Mr. Robot and His Robot Factory is a platform game created for the Atari 8-bit family by Ron Rosen and published in 1983 by Datamost. The music was composed by Gary Gilbertson using Philip Price's Advanced Music Processor, while the title screen was drawn by Art Huff. It was ported to the Apple II by Robert McNally and the Commodore 64.
The gameplay is similar to that of Miner 2049er. The player controls a humanoid robot that must traverse all of the platforms in a factory filled with ladders, conveyor belts, and other gadgetry.
The game includes a built-in level editor.

Genere: Platform 

Valutazione: N/A
